## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

❌ **Skipping deep research**: PESTEL requires 35-55 operations, not 6 quick searches
❌ **Generic PESTEL**: "France has regulations" (not specific GDPR articles and implications)
❌ **Shallow Legal factor**: Missing GDPR articles, AI Act, or country-specific laws
❌ **Evidence-free SWOT**: Assertions without citing 101 gaps or 105 customer quotes
❌ **Wrong framework for query**: Using BMC when user needs competitive positioning (use SWOT instead)
❌ **E2E mode confusion**: Performing Porter's or BMC in E2E mode (only PESTEL + SWOT in E2E)
❌ **No strategy grounding**: Performing PESTEL/SWOT without reading strategy/ folder first

